    <string name="welcome_view_prevent_frozen">⚠️ Prevent Notable from Being Frozen (Onyx Devices)</string>
    <string name="welcome_view_prevent_frozen_details">"Onyx devices may automatically freeze (kill) apps in the background to save battery. If you do not disable this feature, Notable will be constantly closed when in the background, which can be very annoying and may cause loss of work or interruptions. "</string>
    <string name="welcome_view_prevent_frozen_instructions_title">How to prevent freezing:</string>
    <string name="welcome_view_prevent_frozen_instructions">1. Long press the Notable app icon on the Onyx launcher (home screen).\n2. Select \"Unfreeze app\" from the menu.</string>
    <string name="welcome_view_prevent_frozen_recommended">This step is highly recommended for a smooth experience.</string>
    <string name="welcome_view_quick_start_title"><![CDATA[📖 Quick Start & Gestures Guide]]></string>
    <string name="welcome_view_quick_start_navigation">Navigation</string>
    <string name="welcome_view_quick_start_navigation_details">• Swipe up/down: Scroll page\n• Swipe left/right: Previous/next page\n• Pinch with 2 fingers: Zoom\n• Tap page number: Quick jump\n• Two-finger swipe left/right: Show/hide toolbar</string>
    <string name="welcome_view_quick_start_selection_editing_title"><![CDATA[Selection & Editing]]></string>
    <string name="welcome_view_quick_start_selection_editing_details"><![CDATA[• Hold & drag: Select items\n• Double tap: Undo\n• Double tap on selection: Copy\n• Drag selection: Move\n• Scribble to erase (if enabled)]]></string>
    <string name="welcome_view_quick_start_tips_title">Tips</string>
    <string name="welcome_view_quick_start_tips_details">• Use \'Selection Export\' to quickly share images.\n• Tap the page number to quickly jump between pages.\n• Try enabling \'Scribble to Erase\' in Settings for natural erasing.\n• Double tap to undo, or on a selection to copy it.\n• You can use Notable as a live PDF viewer for LaTeX—see README.\n• You can customize gesture actions in Settings.</string>

